# Security Policy

## Reporting a vulnerability

If you discover a security issue or have concerns about how Xable interacts with repositories:

security@korzent.com

Please include:

- description of the issue  
- steps to reproduce  
- potential impact  
- any relevant files or scenarios  

---

## Scope

This repository is a public playground with intentionally broken scenarios.

Do not submit vulnerabilities related to:
- expected broken behavior in scenarios
- test failures (these are intentional)

---

## Our commitment

We take security seriously.

- Xable operates read-only by default  
- no repository is modified without explicit user approval  
- analysis is limited to selected files  
- private code is not used for model training  

We aim to respond to security reports promptly.
